  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The proposed study will evaluate adult patients admitted to the medical or surgical intensive
      care units (ICUs) at San Francisco General Hospital (SFGH). On admission, patients will be
      randomized in a 1:1 manner to the mini-bronchoalveolar lavage (BAL) quantitative culture arm
      in the setting of suspected ventilator-associated pneumonia (VAP) versus the tracheal
      aspirate culture arm, which is the current test available at SFGH.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients will be randomized to either Mini-Bal or tracheal aspirate then samples will be
      taken to the lab for culture. Comparative analysis will then be performed based upon lab
      results.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
