  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  All adult patients (&gt; age 18) admitted to 5E, 5R, and 4E intensive care units and are
             on the ventilator for greater than 48 hours and expected to remain on the ventilator
             for awhile

          -  Study procedures would be performed only in patients clinically suspected of having
             VAP.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Severe respiratory distress at the time of suspected VAP defined by:

               -  FiO2 ≥ 0.7

               -  PEEP ≥ 12
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
